---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Change Log - CLIF Data Dictionary"
  description="Version history and changes to the Common Longitudinal ICU data Format"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-clif-burgundy mb-8">CLIF Data Dictionary Change Log</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="text-xl mb-8">
        Track the evolution of the Common Longitudinal ICU data Format (CLIF) through its version
        history. This change log documents all updates, improvements, and structural changes to the
        data dictionary.
      </p>

      <!-- Version 2.1.0 -->
      <section class="mb-12 bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-clif-burgundy mb-4">
          Version 2.1.0 <span class="text-lg font-normal text-gray-600">(September 2025)</span>
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Data Structure Updates</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>
            Move Code Status, CRRT therapy, ECMO MCS, Hospital Diagnosis, Medication Administered Intermittent, Microbiology Culture, Micro non-culture, and Patient Procedures to Beta status
          </li>
          <li>
            Finalize patient language category mCIDE –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/13"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#13</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Add ADT location type field with finalized mCIDE –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/39"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#39</a
            >,
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/64"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#64</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Finalize hospitalization admission type mCIDE –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/16"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#16</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Add LTACH to hospital_type mCIDE
          </li>
          <li>
            Revision to Micro culture mCIDE for LOINC compatibility –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/25"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#25</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Finalize patient language category mCIDE –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/13"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#13</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Add ADT location type field with finalized mCIDE –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/39"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#39</a
            >,
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/64"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#64</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Finalize hospitalization admission type mCIDE (Add LTACH to admission_type mCIDE) –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/39"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#39</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Additional information on hospitalization variables for ADI/SVI
          </li>
          <li>
            Addition of device_id to respiratory_support
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/67"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#67</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Version 2.0.0 -->
      <section
        class="mb-12 bg-clif-burgundy-light/10 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-clif-burgundy/20"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-clif-burgundy mb-4">
          Version 2.0.0
          <span class="text-lg font-normal text-gray-600">(February 2025)</span>
          <span class="ml-2 bg-clif-burgundy text-white text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full"
            >Current Version</span
          >
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Major ERD Upgrade</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Combined patient and hospitalization tables for improved data structure</li>
          <li>Introduced maturity concept for ERD and tables (Beta, Concept, Future)</li>
          <li>Added comprehensive Beta tables with production-ready structures</li>
          <li>Defined concept tables for future implementation</li>
          <li>Standardized mCIDE (minimum Common ICU Data Elements) across all tables</li>
          <li>
            Standardized all datetime variables to be time zone aware with UTC format
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/40"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >(Issue #40)</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Revision to Micro culture mCIDE for LOINC compatibility –
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues/25"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline"
              >Issue#25</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-clif-burgundy-light/15 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm">
            <strong>Note:</strong> This version represents a major restructuring of the CLIF data format
            with significant improvements to standardization and interoperability across institutions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Version 1.0.0 -->
      <section class="mb-12 bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-clif-burgundy mb-4">Version 1.0.0</h2>

        <p class="mb-4">First official release of the Common Longitudinal ICU data Format (CLIF)</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Initial table structure definitions</li>
          <li>Core entity-relationship model</li>
          <li>Foundation for multi-institutional critical care data standardization</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Links Section -->
      <section class="mt-12 p-6 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Related Resources</h2>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p>
            <a href="/data-dictionary" class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline font-medium">
              → View Current Data Dictionary (v2.0.0)
            </a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a
              href="/data-dictionary/data-dictionary-2.1.0"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline font-medium"
            >
              → View Data Dictionary v2.1.0 (Coming Soon)
            </a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a
              href="/data-dictionary/data-dictionary-1.0.0"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline font-medium"
            >
              → View Data Dictionary v1.0.0 (Deprecated)
            </a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/Common-Longitudinal-ICU-data-Format/CLIF/issues"
              class="text-clif-burgundy hover:underline font-medium"
            >
              → GitHub Issues Tracker
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
